      <section id="details">
        <h2 class="gem-c-heading gem-c-heading--font-size-27 gem-c-heading--mobile-top-margin  ">Details</h2>


        
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
    
          <div class="govspeak">
<p>The <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/adult-social-care-infection-control-fund" class="govuk-link">Adult Social Care Infection Control Fund</a> was <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/care-home-support-package-backed-by-600-million-to-help-reduce-coronavirus-infections" class="govuk-link">first introduced in May 2020</a> and was initially worth £600 million.</p>

<p>Its supports adult social care providers to reduce the rate of coronavirus (COVID-19) transmission within and between care settings, in particular by helping to reduce the need for staff movements between sites.</p>

<p>The Adult Social Care Infection Control Fund has been extended until March 2021, with an extra £546 million of funding.</p>
</div>

</div>
      </section>
    </div>

